<TEXT>
american telephone amp telegraph co is asking 
federal regulators for new flexibility in setting rates for 
business customers to allow the company to compete with discounts 
offered by other longdistance companies 
the new ratesetting method would allow industry leader atampt to 
offer special rate plans to individual businesses that already have 
been offered discount pricing by competing longdistance carriers 
we need to be able to respond to these competitive 
situations larry garfinkel atampt vice president for marketing 
services said tuesday customers would be deprived of the 
benefits of competition if all carriers cannot compete on an equal 
basis 
under federal regulations atampts rates are generally available 
to all customers other longdistance companies whose prices are 
not regulated can tailor their prices for an individual company 
in a filing with the federal communications commission late 
monday atampt said its new ratesetting proposal was prompted by mci 
communications corps discount offering to holiday corp of 
memphis tenn the nations largest hotel chain with more than 
1800 affiliate and franchise hotel properties 
atampt wants to offer pricing discounts to holiday corp 
competitive with mcis proposed plan 
garfinkel said the atampt proposal is absolutely not 
deregulation since the fcc will continue its oversight of atampts 
rates and profits he also said the company will not set prices for 
special packages below cost 
mci said it will oppose atampts proposal as unlawful the 
secondlargest longdistance carrier said the plan would allow atampt 
to ignore longstanding safeguards designed to protect the 
public from predatory pricing and discrimination by any company 
that controls a large share of the market as atampt does providing 
about 72 percent of the countrys longdistance service 
atampt spokesman herb linnen said the timing of the companys 
proposal was coincidental to the fccs preparations this week for 
another step toward radically changing the way atampt is regulated 
the fcc on thursday is expected to unveil a specific proposal to 
put in place a new system of regulating atampt by capping rates 
rather than profits atampt has been lobbying hard for the change 
